    <div class="documentBody">
        <div>
            <p><strong>Political appointments</strong></p>
<p><strong>2000-2001</strong>&nbsp;State Secretary in the Office of the Prime Minister (Stoltenberg I Government).<br /><strong>1992-1996</strong> Political advisor in the Ministry of Fisheries.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Member of the Board of the Labour Party (Nordland)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Bindal local council and its executive committee (16 years)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Deputy Chair of the Labour Party (8 years)</p>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /><strong>Work experience<br /></strong></p>
<p><strong>2008</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;Fish farmer, SinkaBerg-Hansen AS, Rørvik <br /><strong>1996-2000</strong> Home-maker, looking after children<br /><strong>1988-1992</strong>&nbsp;Customer consultant at EWOS A.S., Lørenskog.<br /><strong>1986-1988</strong>&nbsp;Managing Director of Bindalssmolt A.S., Bindal<br /><strong>1985</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Teacher in aquaculture, Ytre Namdal Upper Secondary School, Rørvik<br /><strong>1981-1985</strong>&nbsp;Dental assistant at a number of dental surgeries<br />Between 2001 and 2008, Lisbeth Berg-Hansen was employed full-time on boards and committees.</p>
<p><strong>Board appointments<br />Previously</strong></p>
<p><strong>2002-2008</strong> Member of the Executive Committee and Board of Directors of the Confederation of Norwegian Enterprise <br /><strong>2004-2008</strong> Vice President of the Confederation of Norwegian Enterprise <br />Board Member and Deputy Chair of the Norwegian Institute of Fisheries and Aquaculture, Tromsø<br />Member of the Board of the Nordland Research Institute, Bodø<br />Chair of the Board of the Norwegian Seafood Federation (FHL)<br />Chair of the FHL Aquaculture Division<br />Chair of the Council of <em>Kysten inn i EU</em><br />Member of the Europe Committee of the Confederation of Norwegian Enterprise<br />Member of the Europe Committee of the Labour Party<br />Chair of Kjella Helselag (National Association for Public Health)<br />Chair of the Forum for Active Ownership and Family-owned companies (Confederation of Norwegian Enterprise)<br />Member of the Board of Aker Seafoods ASA<br />Member of the Board of Fosen ASA<br />Deputy Chair of the Board of the Institute of Marine Research<br />Deputy Chair of the Board of Bodø University College<br />Member of the Board of KLV (National Knowledge Centre for Salmon and the Aquatic Environment)<br />Member of the Board of the family-owned company SinkaBerg-Hansen AS<br />Member of the Board of SOS Children’s Villages, Norway<br />Member of the Board of Investinor AS<br />Member of the Government’s Expert Committee on the High North<br />Member of the Board of Fiskeribladet Fiskaren AS<br />Chair of the Board of Bindal Kraftlag SA<br />Member of the Control Committee of the Confederation of Norwegian Enterprise<br />Deputy Member of Council of Representatives of DnB Nor<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /><strong></strong></p>
<p><strong>Education</strong><br /></p><strong></strong>
<p><strong>1969-1978</strong> &nbsp;Kjella School, Bindal (primary/lower secondary) <br /><strong>1979-1980</strong> &nbsp;Asphaugen Upper Secondary School, Bodø – Dental Assistant <br /><strong>1983-1984</strong>&nbsp; Ytre Namdal Upper Secondary, Rørvik - VK1 Aquaculture <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Various courses on aquaculture</p>
<p><br /><strong>Other</strong><br /><strong></strong></p>
<p><strong>2004 &nbsp;</strong>Member of the Grønnevet commission<br /><strong>2008</strong> &nbsp;Contributed to the Norwegian Official Report on Vocational Training in the Future<br /></p>
